# PoseFlow Core ML Repository Setup

The goal is to initialize the new PoseFlow repository (`https://github.com/maheshwari-aniruddh/PoseFlow`) with only the core machine learning and pose detection logic, excluding the full web app and other auxiliary files for now.

## User Review Required

> [!IMPORTANT]
> I will be pushing to `https://github.com/maheshwari-aniruddh/PoseFlow`. Please ensure you have the necessary permissions and that the repository is ready to receive pushes.

## Proposed Core Files

The following files are identified as the "core ML/MediaFlow" logic:
- [config.py](file:///Users/aniruddhmodi/Documents/PycharmProjects/Yogabuddy-backup-original/config.py): Core settings and pose definitions.
- [pose_detector.py](file:///Users/aniruddhmodi/Documents/PycharmProjects/Yogabuddy-backup-original/pose_detector.py): MediaPipe integration.
- [pose_classifier.py](file:///Users/aniruddhmodi/Documents/PycharmProjects/Yogabuddy-backup-original/pose_classifier.py): KNN classification logic.
- [form_corrector.py](file:///Users/aniruddhmodi/Documents/PycharmProjects/Yogabuddy-backup-original/form_corrector.py): Real-time feedback logic.
- [session_tracker.py](file:///Users/aniruddhmodi/Documents/PycharmProjects/Yogabuddy-backup-original/session_tracker.py): Progress and scoring.
- [nlg_engine.py](file:///Users/aniruddhmodi/Documents/PycharmProjects/Yogabuddy-backup-original/nlg_engine.py): Feedback generation.
- [utils/angles.py](file:///Users/aniruddhmodi/Documents/PycharmProjects/Yogabuddy-backup-original/utils/angles.py): Joint angle calculations.
- `models/`: Trained pose classification models.
- [pose_landmarker_full.task](file:///Users/aniruddhmodi/Documents/PycharmProjects/Yogabuddy-backup-original/pose_landmarker_full.task): MediaPipe model file.
- [requirements.txt](file:///Users/aniruddhmodi/Documents/PycharmProjects/Yogabuddy-backup-original/requirements.txt): Necessary Python dependencies.

## Repository Strategy

1.  Add a new git remote: `poseflow-origin`.
2.  Create a new orphan branch `core-ml` to ensure a clean history without the web app.
3.  Add and commit only the specified files.
4.  Push to the `main` branch of the new repository.

## Verification Plan

### Automated Verification
- Run `git ls-tree` on the target branch to ensure only the intended files are present.
- Run a basic pose detection test to ensure the core logic is still functional in isolation.
